--- groovy ---
groovy|g path scriptname [args]

runs the specified groovy script with the string args in argument.

path: the path to the script.
scriptname: name of the script.

Example:
--------
  lsfw> groovy /path/to/script srvbyport.groovy 80 110 25

Runs the groovy script 'srvbyport.groovy' in '/path/to/script' with arguments
'80 110 25'
